
<form
    id="settings_spoolman"
    class="form-horizontal"
>
    <h3>
        Spoolman
        <small>{{ _('Version') }}:
            <span data-bind="text: pluginSettings.installed_version"></span>
        </small>
    </h3>
    <div class="tabbable">
        <ul
            class="nav nav-tabs"
            id="spoolmanger-settings-tab"
        >
            <li class="active">
                <a
                    href="#tab-spoolman-General"
                    data-toggle="tab"
                >
                    General
                </a>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <div class="tab-content">
            <!-- Tab: General -->
            <div
                id="tab-spoolman-General"
                class="tab-pane active"
            >
                <div class="control-group">
                    <label
                        class="control-label"
                        for="settings-spoolman-general-spoolmanUrl"
                    >
                        Spoolman instance URL
                    </label>
                    <div class="controls">
                        <input
                            id="settings-spoolman-general-spoolmanUrl"
                            type="text"
                            class="input-xlarge text-left"
                            data-bind="textInput: pluginSettings.spoolmanUrl"
                            placeholder="https://192.168.1.100:7912"
                        >
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="control-group">
                    <label
                        class="control-label"
                        for="settings-spoolman-general-isSpoolmanCertVerifyEnabled"
                    >
                        Verify SSL certificate (if applicable)
                    </label>
                    <div class="controls">
                        <div>
                            <input
                                id="settings-spoolman-general-isSpoolmanCertVerifyEnabled"
                                type="checkbox"
                                class="text-left"
                                data-bind="checked: pluginSettings.isSpoolmanCertVerifyEnabled"
                            >
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="control-group">
                    <label
                        class="control-label"
                        for="settings-spoolman-general-spoolmanCertPemPath"
                    >
                        SSL certificate <code>.pem</code> path
                    </label>
                    <div class="controls">
                        <div>
                            <input
                                id="settings-spoolman-general-spoolmanCertPemPath"
                                type="text"
                                class="input-xlarge text-left"
                                data-bind="textInput: pluginSettings.spoolmanCertPemPath"
                                placeholder="/path/to/cert.pem"
                            >
                        </div>
                        <div style="margin-top: 0.25em">
                            <small>
                                In case your Spoolman instance is using an SSL certificate which is unavailable to your Octoprint instance (eg. self-signed certificate), you can provide a path to custom certificate chain file. This allows the plugin to establish secure connection without disabling certificate verification. The file must be located on Octoprint's machine, and should be readable for Octoprint.
                            </small>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <hr/>
                </div>
                <div class="control-group">
                    <label
                        class="control-label"
                        for="settings-spoolman-general-isPreprintSpoolVerifyEnabled"
                    >
                        Verify spools before print
                    </label>
                    <div class="controls">
                        <div>
                            <input
                                id="settings-spoolman-general-isPreprintSpoolVerifyEnabled"
                                type="checkbox"
                                class="text-left"
                                data-bind="checked: pluginSettings.isPreprintSpoolVerifyEnabled"
                            >
                        </div>
                        <div style="margin-top: 0.25em">
                            <small>
                                Spools verification displays a modal after clicking the 'Print' button, which presents all necessary info & warnings before the actual print job starts. It allows the user to either confirm (and start the print) or cancel the job. Verification consists of: checking remaining filament, checking spool selection, detecting tools count mismatch (multi-tool printers).
                            </small>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</form>
